    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-19T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-19T07:00:00-05:00" n="975"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d975">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/7–1954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-19T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 19, 1954—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 660. Limit distribution. <persName
                        corresp="#p_AWD1">Dennis Allen</persName> has just informed us that London
                    has cleared <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>‘s messages to Colombo
                    powers, Australia and New Zealand (<gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss>s
                        644<note n="1" xml:id="d975fn1">Dated July 18, <ref target="#pg_1434">p.
                            1434</ref>.</note> and 649<note n="2" xml:id="d975fn2">Dated July 18,
                            <ref target="#pg_1439">p. 1439</ref>.</note>) including suggestion for
                    statements along lines of proposed United States unilateral declaration in event
                    of Geneva settlement and instructed that messages be delivered immediately.</p>
                <p>We will be discussing with British today program of action to be taken in event
                    agreement reached at conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
